BaselineStore manages content-addressed baseline files in .drift/baselines/. Each file is named by its hash. For markers, the hash is sha1(content). For specs, the hash is the canonical hash (sha1 of spec content with &lt;ref&gt; tags stripped, see scanner.spec_discovery); the file content is the raw innerxml including refs so that drift diff and drift show display faithful spec text. Write stores content at &lt;hash&gt; if absent (dedup) and does NOT verify sha1(content)==hash for the spec case. Read returns content for &lt;hash&gt; or false if missing. Delete removes a single file. Missing files are not errors. See principles.specs_are_truth — content-addressed by canonical hash.